<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Please accept this letter as notice of my resignation from the position of Web Developer at Company X.</span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Although this has been a difficult decision to make, I have been offered an opportunity that I believe will help me reach my long-term career goals. I hope you will understand my reasons for moving on.</span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">As per the terms of my employment contract, I will continue to work for the company for the next 30 days, completing my employment on <strong>DD/MM/YYYY</strong>. If there are any areas in particular you would like me to focus on during my notice period, please let me know.</span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">But of course, i really wannaÂ </span><span class="s1">terminate as</span><span class="s1">Â soon as possible</span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">I very much enjoyed being able to work with you all. I would have stayed but for this irresistible offer. I thank you for the cooperative, helpful and supportive working environment you all contributed to provide and I hope that we remain in touch.</span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">You've all made showing up to work something I was looking forward to every business day of the week</span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Wishing you all the best and again, let's stay in touch</span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Regards,</span></p>
